## Your Team Is Doing SEO — But Is It Actually Working?

In-house teams often know what SEO activity looks like: publishing content, fixing technical issues, monitoring rankings. What's harder to assess is whether those activities are the right ones for your specific competitive position — and whether they're being executed in the sequence that builds momentum rather than producing isolated, short-lived results.

Common symptoms: content that ranks briefly then disappears, technical fixes that don't move rankings, a growing archive of blog posts that collectively attract less traffic than expected. These aren't effort problems. They're direction problems.

SEO consulting provides the strategic layer your team is missing. Expert guidance on what to prioritise, what to stop, and what sequence of actions builds compound growth — delivered in focused sessions that give your team confidence to execute independently.

**First session from £200.** No retainer required. Most clients identify immediate improvements in the first session and see results before deciding on ongoing engagement.

